name: Plush Quaggan Backpack
description: <c=@flavor>No quaggans were harmed in the making of this backpack.</c>

name: Durmand's Pen
description: <c=@flavor>It's said that the pen is mightier...</c>

name: Golden Relic of Rin
description: <c=@flavor>Pillaged long ago from the ruined city of Rin.</c>

name: Consortium Charm
description:
Guaranteed* to protect against any of a multitude of threats and indignities!

*Guarantee not legally binding.

name: Halfmad's Mug
description: <c=@flavor>Claimed to be the property of Brothander Halfmad, creator of Bear's Brown Ale, and the first norn to bring the art of brewing to his people.</c>

name: Appleseller's Lucky Cog
description: <c=@flavor>Smooth from having constantly been toyed with, the initials TL are etched roughly into the metal.</c>

name: Marriner's Flask
description: <c=@flavor>Said to have been the property of the legendary Cobiah Marriner, founder of Lion's Arch.</c>

name: Fierceshot's Arrowhead
description: <c=@flavor>Said to have belonged to the legendary charr archer Pyre Fierceshot.</c>

name: Magister's Field Journal
description: <c=@flavor>A collection of clever, dreamy notes penned in a flowing hand.</c>

name: Althea's Ashes
description: <c=@flavor>The legendary beauty who captured the heart of Prince Rurik, only to perish in the Searing of Ascalon.</c>

name: Plague Idol
description: <c=@flavor>An ancient relic of old Cantha, from the time of its corruption by the Deceiver's dark magic.</c>

name: Matriarch's Quill
description: <c=@flavor>Some of the savage power of the harpy that once wore this feather still resides in it.</c>

name: Zinn's Data Crystal
description: <c=@flavor>A rare copy of Zinn's research into the power of souls.</c>

name: Experiment ZX-27115
description: <c=@flavor>The label reads: "Danger." It hums pleasantly.</c>

name: Imperial Chef Yileng's Golden Spoon
description: <c=@flavor>The legendary chef gave these to his finest students.</c>

name: Gargoyle Skull
description: <c=@flavor>A remnant of the presumed-extinct gargoyles.</c>

name: Egg of the Crystal Queen
description: <c=@flavor>These undeveloped eggs were supposedly found in the lair of Glint, the dragon oracle.</c>

name: Celestial Sigil
description: <c=@flavor>A prized possession of guilds in ancient times.</c>

name: Thackeray Family Crest
description: <c=@flavor>Family crest of the famous Thackerays.</c>

name: Mark of the Imperial Guard
description: <c=@flavor>Formerly worn by a member of the Imperial Guards of Cantha.</c>

name: Collar of the First Commissar
description: <c=@flavor>Rumored to be worn by the first dredge to break free from dwarven slavery.</c>

name: Gwen's Necklace
description: <c=@flavor>Given to Gwen by her beloved Keiran.</c>

name: The Sleeping Seed
description: <c=@flavor>This mysterious seed appears to be dormant.</c>

name: Hymn to the Prophets
description: <c=@flavor>Straight from the dark depths of krait-infested waters.</c>

name: Call of the Wild
description: <c=@flavor>Audible to those who seek their legend.</c>

name: Mark of the Tethyos Houses
description: <c=@flavor>This must have once belonged to a victim of a largos assassin.</c>

name: Jade Wind Orb
description: <c=@flavor>This relic of long-forgotten Cantha contains air captured from the Jade Winds.</c>

name: Symbol of the Deceiver
description: <c=@flavor>Some say the great deceiver of Cantha was a victim of the fates. Others call him a traitor.</c>

name: Godrock Amulet
description: <c=@flavor>Once an object of worship among the grawl.</c>

name: Conundrum of Maut
description: <c=@flavor>Maut's frustrations forever locked away.</c>

name: The Heart of Mellaggan
description: <c=@flavor>A precious jewel found in the depths of the ocean.</c>

name: Blood of the Khan-Ur
description: <c=@flavor>Forged in the blazing fires of the Black Citadel's foundry.</c>

name: Jewel of Ahdashim
description: <c=@flavor>The crown jewel from the vaults of Ahdashim.</c>

name: The Eyes of Abaddon
description: <c=@flavor>They burn with the fire of a forgotten god.</c>

name: Feather of the Owl
description: <c=@flavor>This feather is said to have fallen from the spirit of Owl before being destroyed by Jormag.</c>

description: <c=@flavor>An exotic gift that speaks of faraway lands.</c>

name: Syzygy
description: <c=@flavor>A powerful alignment.</c>

name: Limited-Use Thornroot Finisher

name: Limited-Use Super Explosive Finisher
description: Blast your opponents with this Super Adventure Box Super Bomb finishing move in PvP and WvW.

name: Preserved Red Iris Flower
description: <c=@flavor>Lovingly preserved specimen of an exceedingly rare iris.</c>

name: Kurzick Bauble
description: <c=@flavor>Smuggled out of Cantha long ago, a relic of the Great House of Lutgardis.</c>

name: Warmaster's Family Heirloom
description: <c=@flavor>Generations of norn-etched runes cover this dolyak horn. The most recent is a symbol of the Vigil.</c>

name: Totem of the Gorilla
description: <c=@flavor>An intrepid norn artist paid respect to a far-flung Spirit of the Wild with this carving.</c>

name: Fledgling Charm
description: <c=@flavor>Young tengu are given charms like this for protection.</c>

name: Anton's Secret
description: <c=@flavor>An item to be hidden in the most unlikely of places.</c>

name: Passiflora Karkinata
description: <c=@flavor>An extremely rare and powerful floral specimen.</c>

name: Ancient Karka Carapace
description: <c=@flavor>Part of the ancient karka that attacked Lion's Arch. Mysterious magics seem to be woven into its chitinous shell.</c>

name: Molten Ore
description: <c=@flavor>A dark artifact of the combined forces of the Flame Legion and dredge. This ore seems too impure to properly refine, but it gleams with dark potential.</c>

name: Big Mama's Tooth
description: <c=@flavor>Legends speak of "Big Mama," the largest drake broodmother that ever lived. If she still does, it seems she's short at least one tooth.</c>

name: Amulet of Protection
description: <c=@flavor>Stolen from the body of a long-forgotten lord during the Guild Wars.</c>

name: Salma's Diamond Jubilee Necklace
description: <c=@flavor>Queen Salma's reign was long and prosperous. Such prosperity has long been missed in Kryta.<c>

name: Kodan Prayer Beads
description: <c=@flavor>A string of 49 ivory beads.</c>

name: Amulet of the Skies
description: <c=@flavor>A talented Durmand Priory scholar based this necklace on ancient astrological charts found on jotun megaliths.</c>

name: Petrified Skull Juju
description: <c=@flavor>An ancient relic of the mystic beings of Echovald Forest.</c>

name: Nornbear's Remembrance
description: <c=@flavor>Once a painful reminder to Jora of her brother's curse.</c>

name: Archaic Grawl Necklace
description: <c=@flavor>From a time before the grawl had a spoken language.</c>

name: The Southsun Rose
description: <c=@flavor>The largest pink diamond in all of Tyria.</c>

name: Charisma
description: <c=@flavor>The locket contains a picture of Kolijn Johansson, Trade Administrator of Hoelbrak.</c>

name: Third-Place Medal
description: <c=@flavor>Congratulations from the Divinity's Reach Fancy Cat Association! Everyone is fancy in their own way.</c>

name: Prayer to Otter
description: <c=@flavor>Otter is a fickle spirit, but when she does grant a boon, it is a powerful gift indeed.</c>

name: The Queen's Necklace
description: <c=@flavor>Commissioned for Queen Jennah by a council member, but found too ornate for her tastes.</c>

name: Luxon Pendant
description: <c=@flavor>Smuggled out of Cantha long ago, a relic of the Serpent Clan.<c>

name: The Beetlestone Diamond
description: <c=@flavor>Mined from the Onyx Fields of Southsun Cove for the pleasure of Lord Beetlestone.</c>

name: Protomatter Chain
description: <c=@flavor>Some strange, ethereal material from the Mists has solidified into this odd necklace.</c>
